From 42a6717a10abd197d1eb654a7487575874c5ef48 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Danny <danny.trev21@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Mar 2026 10:19:25 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat: implement interactive phases 5-7 for 7-phase
 negotiation protocol
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Extends the negotiation pipeline from 4 phases to 7 interactive LLM phases
as specified in the production spec (specify-production-spec.md):

- Phase 5: Interactive Invariant Extraction — extracts invariants from AC text,
  constitution security rules, and data model inference with human-in-the-loop
- Phase 6: Completeness Sweep & Routing — runs standardized checklist across
  13 categories (auth, errors, rate limiting, etc.) and assigns verification skills
- Phase 7: EARS Formalization — synthesizes all outputs into structured EARS
  statements using 5 patterns (UBIQUITOUS, EVENT_DRIVEN, STATE_DRIVEN, UNWANTED, OPTIONAL)

Also includes:
- Deterministic validation functions for phases 5-7 (Block Principle 1)
- Mock responses for all 3 new phases
- Web UI updated to 7-phase flow with feedback support
- Compiler and synthesis updated to handle new invariant/EARS formats
- 42 new tests (TDD: RED then GREEN), all 392 tests passing

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
